column2: Self-motivated and self-oriented. Inclined to map out an independent life path and follow personal direction, experiencing difficulties only when others interfere. Values independence and enjoys solitude. Appreciates the company of others, but only when given plenty of freedom for personal pursuits. Tendency toward egocentric and selfish behavior requires monitoring.

Identity and personal resources form the basis of all other success. Requires internal security before stepping out into the world. Family roots and home environment provide foundations for self-discovery and self-knowledge that form the foundation for future success. Risk of becoming overly reclusive requires attention.

Interactions with other people take on a paramount role. Values both personal relationships and broader human connections. Possesses a gift for mediating relationships through insight into relational nuances. Self-discovery occurs primarily within the context of relationships. Risk of becoming engulfed in stifling relationships requires vigilance.

Public life represents the pinnacle of fulfillment. Personal satisfaction derives from worldly achievements, with self-knowledge gained through public position. The need for high public profile manifests through both career and social status. Risk that achievements may come at the expense of loved ones requires consideration.
